QUESTION :
Sample Problem 3: Digging a Road Through Rugged Terrain

You’re tasked with building a road through rugged terrain. Each segment has a known sea level height:

Input: [-1, 1, 1, 1]

To ensure safe construction, the terrain must be transformed into a strictly downward slope, meaning:

Code
L[0] > L[1] > L[2] > L[3]
🛠️ Digging Rule

On day D, your digging team can reduce the sea level of any scheduled segment by:

Code
2D - 1 meters
You can assign multiple segments to be dug on the same day, and dig the same segment on multiple days.

🎯 Objective

Find the minimum number of days required to transform the terrain into a strictly decreasing sequence.

✅ Output: 3

📈 One Possible Strategy

Day 1: Dig segments 1 and 4 → reduce by 1 meter
Result: [-1, 0, 1, 0]

Day 2: Dig segments 3 and 4 → reduce by 3 meters
Result: [-1, 0, -2, -2]

Day 3: Dig segments 2, 3, and 4 → reduce by 5 meters
Final: [-1, -5, -7, -9]

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SOLUTION:
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <cmath>
#include <algorithm>

using namespace std;

int main() {
    
    int n;
    cin >> n;

    vector<int> arr(n);
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        cin >> arr[i];

    vector<int> target(n);
    target[0] = arr[0];

    for(int i = 1; i < n; i++)
        target[i] = target[i-1] - 1;

    vector<int> diff(n);
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        diff[i] = max(0, arr[i] - target[i]);

    vector<int> each_segment(n,0);
    for(int i = 1; i < n; i++)
        each_segment[i] = ceil(sqrt(diff[i]));

    int days = *max_element(each_segment.begin(), each_segment.end());

    cout << days;

    return 0;
}
